==English==

===Noun===
'''[[allative]] [[case]]'''

#{{grammar}}: [[case]] used to indicate movement onto, or to the [[adjacent|adjacency]] of something. In English, this is usually expressed by the prepositions '''to''' or '''onto''', as in "to the house," "onto the house." Languages that use the allative case include [[Dyirbal]], [[Finnish]], [[Hungarian]], [[Estonian]], and [[Lithuanian]].

